      "The main hazards to control are heat stress, heat exhaustion, heat stroke, dehydration. On a real site, those hazards rarely stand alone: they usually overlap with access, supervision, training, emergency response, public protection, equipment condition, and nearby trades. This article separates legal requirements from best practice and field checklist items so a reader does not mistake a sample procedure for law.",
