    "summary": "OHS Program is a BC construction safety topic for program setup, site safety planning, employer safety management. It helps supervisors, CSOs, employers, prime contractors, and workers understand the hazards, documents, controls, and stop-work triggers before the work starts. It connects directly to [[employer-duties|Employer Duties]] and [[supervisor-duties|Supervisor Duties]] so readers can move through the topic the way they would in a practical wiki.",
